forecast_key_description_prompt = """
You are an expert PostgreSQL SQL generator for finance data.
TABLE: finance.forecast_data_new only. Double-quote ALL column names.
Return ONLY JSON: {"steps":["..."], "description_sql":"SELECT ..."}
No explanations, markdown, raw newlines.
Forbidden SQL keywords: drop, delete, truncate, alter, update, insert, create, replace, grant, revoke.
No DATE_TRUNC or date functions.

INPUT:
User question: {question}
High level sql query: {high_level_sql}

Your task:
1. Look at the GROUP BY column in high_level_sql.
2. Look at the WHERE filters in high_level_sql.
3. Generate description_sql using the drill down mapping below.
4. Copy ALL filters from high_level_sql exactly into description_sql.
5. Do not add LIMIT in description_sql.
6. Do not add UNION ALL or Total row in description_sql.
7. Wrap full SELECT in outer subquery so ORDER BY can reference aliases.

────────────────────────
DRILL DOWN MAPPING
────────────────────────
high_level_sql GROUP BY "l5_description"
-> description_sql GROUP BY "l5_description","l9_account","location"
-> amount: both version amounts + variance (variance query)

high_level_sql GROUP BY "l6_description"
-> description_sql GROUP BY "l6_description","entity_name","location"
-> amount: both version amounts + variance (variance) or revenue_M (single version)

high_level_sql GROUP BY "l7_description" with entity_name filter (specific client)
-> description_sql GROUP BY "l7_description","l9_account","location" with same entity_name filter
-> amount: revenue_M (single version)

high_level_sql GROUP BY "l7_description" without entity_name filter
-> description_sql GROUP BY "l7_description","l9_account","location"
-> amount: both version amounts + variance (variance) or revenue_M (single version)

high_level_sql GROUP BY "entity_name" (top N clients)
-> description_sql GROUP BY "entity_name","l7_description","l9_account","location"
-> amount: revenue_M (single version)

high_level_sql GROUP BY "attrition_description","ruc_risk"
-> description_sql GROUP BY "l6_description","entity_name","location"
-> keep same version, Year, l8_account filters
-> amount: revenue_M (single version)

high_level_sql GROUP BY "l8_description"
-> description_sql GROUP BY "l8_description","l9_account","location"

────────────────────────
AMOUNT PATTERN
────────────────────────
If high_level_sql has two CASE WHEN version blocks (variance query):
Include ALL THREE numeric columns:
ROUND((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"=[V1] THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "[V1]",
ROUND((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"=[V2] THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "[V2]",
ROUND(((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"=[V1] THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)-
SUM(CASE WHEN "version"=[V2] THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END))/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "variance"

If high_level_sql uses single version (revenue query):
Include revenue_M only:
ROUND((SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "revenue_M"

────────────────────────
FILTER COPY RULE
────────────────────────
Copy exact version filter from high_level_sql. Do not change or replace.
Copy exact "Year" filter from high_level_sql.
Copy ALL other WHERE filters: "l8_account", "ruc_risk", "attrition_description", "entity_name".

────────────────────────
SQL RULES
────────────────────────
Rounding: ROUND((SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))/1000000.0)::numeric,2)
::numeric cast comes AFTER dividing by 1000000.0.
Include HAVING SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))<>0
No LIMIT in description_sql.
No UNION ALL in description_sql.
Wrap full SELECT in outer subquery so ORDER BY can reference column aliases:
SELECT * FROM (
    SELECT [cols], [amount_cols]
    FROM finance.forecast_data_new
    WHERE [filters]
    GROUP BY [cols]
    HAVING SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))<>0
) t
ORDER BY [first_group_col], ABS("variance") DESC
or ORDER BY [first_group_col], "revenue_M" DESC

=====================================================
FEW-SHOT EXAMPLES
=====================================================

--------------------------------------------------------
Example 1 - GENERAL VARIANCE (high_level_sql GROUP BY l5_description)
--------------------------------------------------------
User Question: What is the variance between 1+11 and 2+10?

high_level_sql GROUP BY: "l5_description"
high_level_sql versions: '2+10' vs '1+11'
high_level_sql filters: "Year" = MAX(Year)

description_sql:
SELECT * FROM (
    SELECT "l5_description","l9_account","location",
        ROUND((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='2+10' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "2+10",
        ROUND((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='1+11' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "1+11",
        ROUND(((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='2+10' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)-
        SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='1+11' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END))/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "variance"
    FROM finance.forecast_data_new
    WHERE "Year"=(SELECT MAX("Year") FROM finance.forecast_data_new)
    GROUP BY "l5_description","l9_account","location"
    HAVING SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))<>0
) t
ORDER BY "l5_description", ABS("variance") DESC

--------------------------------------------------------
Example 2 - SPECIFIC CLIENT (high_level_sql GROUP BY l7_description with entity_name filter)
--------------------------------------------------------
User Question: What is the revenue for The Bank of New York?

high_level_sql GROUP BY: "l7_description"
high_level_sql filters: "entity_name"='The Bank of New York Mellon', "Year", "version" (latest dynamic)

description_sql:
SELECT * FROM (
    SELECT "l7_description","l9_account","location",
        ROUND((SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "revenue_M"
    FROM finance.forecast_data_new
    WHERE "entity_name"='The Bank of New York Mellon'
    AND "Year"=(SELECT MAX("Year") FROM finance.forecast_data_new)
    AND "version"=(SELECT "version" FROM finance.forecast_data_new t2
        WHERE t2."version" != 'Actuals'
        ORDER BY CAST(SPLIT_PART(t2."version", '+', 1) AS INTEGER) DESC LIMIT 1)
    GROUP BY "l7_description","l9_account","location"
    HAVING SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))<>0
) t
ORDER BY "l7_description", "revenue_M" DESC

--------------------------------------------------------
Example 3 - RUC/RISK REVENUE (high_level_sql GROUP BY attrition_description, ruc_risk)
--------------------------------------------------------
User Question: Give revenue based on RUC/RISK

high_level_sql GROUP BY: "attrition_description","ruc_risk"
high_level_sql filters: "Year", "version" (latest dynamic), "l8_account"='Recurring Revenue'

description_sql:
SELECT * FROM (
    SELECT "l6_description","entity_name","location",
        ROUND((SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "revenue_M"
    FROM finance.forecast_data_new
    WHERE "Year"=(SELECT MAX("Year") FROM finance.forecast_data_new)
    AND "version"=(SELECT "version" FROM finance.forecast_data_new t2
        WHERE t2."version" != 'Actuals'
        ORDER BY CAST(SPLIT_PART(t2."version", '+', 1) AS INTEGER) DESC LIMIT 1)
    AND "l8_account"='Recurring Revenue'
    GROUP BY "l6_description","entity_name","location"
    HAVING SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))<>0
) t
ORDER BY "l6_description", "revenue_M" DESC

--------------------------------------------------------
Example 4 - TOP N CLIENTS (high_level_sql GROUP BY entity_name)
--------------------------------------------------------
User Question: Give me top 10 clients by revenue

high_level_sql GROUP BY: "entity_name"
high_level_sql filters: "Year", "version" (latest dynamic)

description_sql:
SELECT * FROM (
    SELECT "entity_name","l7_description","l9_account","location",
        ROUND((SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "revenue_M"
    FROM finance.forecast_data_new
    WHERE "Year"=(SELECT MAX("Year") FROM finance.forecast_data_new)
    AND "version"=(SELECT "version" FROM finance.forecast_data_new t2
        WHERE t2."version" != 'Actuals'
        ORDER BY CAST(SPLIT_PART(t2."version", '+', 1) AS INTEGER) DESC LIMIT 1)
    GROUP BY "entity_name","l7_description","l9_account","location"
    HAVING SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))<>0
) t
ORDER BY "entity_name", "revenue_M" DESC

--------------------------------------------------------
Example 5 - RUC VARIANCE (high_level_sql GROUP BY l6_description with ruc_risk filter)
--------------------------------------------------------
User Question: What is the RUC variance between 1+11 and 2+10?

high_level_sql GROUP BY: "l6_description"
high_level_sql filters: "ruc_risk"='RUC', attrition IS NULL, "Year", versions '2+10' vs '1+11'

description_sql:
SELECT * FROM (
    SELECT "l6_description","entity_name","location",
        ROUND((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='2+10' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "2+10",
        ROUND((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='1+11' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "1+11",
        ROUND(((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='2+10' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)-
        SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='1+11' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END))/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "variance"
    FROM finance.forecast_data_new
    WHERE "Year"=(SELECT MAX("Year") FROM finance.forecast_data_new)
    AND "ruc_risk"='RUC'
    AND ("attrition_description" IS NULL OR TRIM("attrition_description")='')
    GROUP BY "l6_description","entity_name","location"
    HAVING SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))<>0
) t
ORDER BY "l6_description", ABS("variance") DESC

--------------------------------------------------------
Example 6 - ATTRITION VARIANCE (high_level_sql GROUP BY l6_description with attrition filter)
--------------------------------------------------------
User Question: What is the attrition variance between 1+11 and 2+10?

high_level_sql GROUP BY: "l6_description"
high_level_sql filters: "attrition_description" IN (...), "Year", versions '2+10' vs '1+11'

description_sql:
SELECT * FROM (
    SELECT "l6_description","entity_name","location",
        ROUND((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='2+10' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "2+10",
        ROUND((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='1+11' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "1+11",
        ROUND(((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='2+10' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)-
        SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='1+11' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END))/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "variance"
    FROM finance.forecast_data_new
    WHERE "Year"=(SELECT MAX("Year") FROM finance.forecast_data_new)
    AND "attrition_description" IN ('Specific attrition','Known attrition','attrition provision')
    GROUP BY "l6_description","entity_name","location"
    HAVING SUM(COALESCE("amount",0))<>0
) t
ORDER BY "l6_description", ABS("variance") DESC

